buildCorpusICmodels(CorpusBasedICModelType, String, ITaxonomy, String, String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.WNSimRepDatasetBuilder
This function creates a collection of node-valued data files containing a structured representation of a set of corpus-based IC models and taxonomical features as described in the paper below: Lastra-Díaz, J.
buildEdgeBasedCondProbCorpusICmodelFiles(CorpusBasedICModelType, String, ITaxonomy, String, String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.WNSimRepDatasetBuilder
This function creates a collection of edge-valued data files containing a structured representation of the CondProbCorpus IC model with different WordNet-based frequency files, as described in the paper below: Lastra-Díaz, J.
buildEdgeInfoCondProbICmodelFiles(String, ITaxonomy, String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.WNSimRepDatasetBuilder
This function creates the edge-based data file for the well-founded CondProb IC models.
buildNodeBasedIntrinsicICmodelFiles(IntrinsicICModelType[], String, ITaxonomy, String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.WNSimRepDatasetBuilder
This function creates a collection of node-valued data files containing a structured representation of a set of intrinsic IC models and taxonomical features as described in the paper below: Lastra-Díaz, J.
buildNonICbasedMeasuresSynsetsBasedFile(SimilarityMeasureType[], String, String, String, IWordNetDB, ITaxonomy, String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.WNSimRepDatasetBuilder
This function creates a collection of synset-valued data files containing the evaluation of a set of non IC-based similarity measures on the input dataset.
buildSynsetsBasedFiles(IntrinsicICModelType[], SimilarityMeasureType[], String, String, String, IWordNetDB, ITaxonomy, String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.WNSimRepDatasetBuilder
This function creates a collection of synset-valued data files containing the evaluation of a set of measures with the input IC models on the input dataset.
buildWNSimRepFiles(String) - Static method in class hesmlclient.HESMLclient
This function builds all the data files in the WNSimRep v1 dataset, which is introduced in the following paper.
